        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 2:40PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 239 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Hendersonville, or 5 miles northeast of Jones Gap
State Park, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flat Rock, Saluda, Jones Gap State Park, Caesars Head State Park,
Dupont State Forest, Tuxedo, North Saluda Reservoir, Crab Creek, and
East Flat Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
